      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "METRO SWISH NZ (1) led from a couple of spots wider and kept kicking for a 1.5m second last time out at Maryborough, making it four minor placings in succession. The hoof is on the till and she has the gate speed to take advantage of the ace draw so could deliver here. PIPALICIOUS (10) kicked off her campaign with three placings before manners let her down last time. Has trialled well since. Draws on the back row but is good enough to overcome that with her A-game. BIG RAIN (6) followed up a debut placing with a fourth as favourite at her most recent appearance at Cranbourne. Has upside. KICKABARREL (11) must be considered after he finished runner-up from this row at Cranbourne last time out.",
